    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a collector-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, maintained in its original sequential twin-turbocharged configuration. The 13B-REW rotary powerplant delivers linear boost through the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 units, with flawless transition at the 4,500 RPM crossover point. Recent diagnostic testing confirms robust compression pulses across all rotor faces, well within factory tolerances. The chassis retains its surgical precision, featuring the original double-wishbone aluminum suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Zero evidence of thermal fatigue on the vacuum harness or apex seal degradation. This is a true survivor with a pristine undercarriage and a crisp, short-throw 5-speed manual transmission.",
      "price": 48500.0,
